data.title: Wallace D. Brown (1985) - Hall of Fame
data.meta_description: Wallace D. Brown, Class: 1963 Induction: 1985 Sport(s): Baseball, Basketball, Football - An honor student and campus leader, Wally Brown was also a leader in athletics
data.text:
An honor student and campus leader, Wally Brown was also a leader in athletics as he led the resurgence of St. Lawrence football in the mid-sixties.

A three-sport letterman, he played basketball and baseball in addition to football and played a major role in the 1962-63 basketball team which posted the best record in 14 years at 15-7. He was cocaptain of the football team and the leading rusher with an average of six yards per carry. His 102 yard reception return set a St. Lawrence record.

He was also president of the L Club and a class officer.
